result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Jerade T. Walker

records.addlTxt: 10:20 AM Defendant Jerade T. Walker in court.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin. Complaint acknowledged, reading waived. DA Kelz states Victim's Rights Legislations have been complied with. Notice of right to attorney given to Defendant  Defendant enters a plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts. Preliminary hearing requested, time limits waived. Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled. Bond already set and is to continue.
Demand for discovery and notice of intent to use DNA

11:54 AM DA calls case and states appearances and possible charges. Jerade T. Walker appeared via video from the Price County Jail. Karl J. Kelz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant's next court date is 10/18/22 at 10 am.  Jail gives Defendant a notice of right to attorney.  Court questions parties as to bond.  DA states bond recommendation of a $500 cash bond with special conditions. No objections to the bond recommendation. Bond ordered as requested.

Defendant may not have contact with the individual(s): M.L.R
**No Contact includes: Going to or remaining in any place the individual resides, is employed at, attends school at, or any public location the individual is temporarily located. Contact through means of telephone. Electronic devices, Social media, email, regular mail, or a 3rd party individual is prohibited. The only exception to this order is contact through your attorney or law enforcement in appropriate circumstances.
